  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Running `npx buidler` when it's not installed results in the following warning:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n> npx buidler\r\nWarning: buidler has been moved to @nomiclabs/buidler\r\nWarning: buidler has been moved to @nomiclabs/buidler\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe message is pretty unclear, it doesn't help you solve the actual issue.\r\n\r\nIt should say something like: \r\n```\r\nError: buidler is not installed, be sure to run `npm install @nomiclabs/buidler`\r\n```",
